# Voxel (in NYC) didn't work
http://unc.dl.sourceforge.net/sourceforge/jode/jode-1.1.2-pre1.jar
http://unc.dl.sourceforge.net/sourceforge/jode/jode-1.1.2-pre1.tar.gz

# Binary (easiest):
cd ~/tmp/
wget http://unc.dl.sourceforge.net/sourceforge/jode/jode-1.1.2-pre1.jar
# and put it on my classpath

You can then decompile a class file with:
  java jode.decompiler.Main --classpath program.jar,libfoo.jar org.package.Class
or a complete package with
  java jode.decompiler.Main --classpath libfoo.jar program.jar

This didn't work on an enum class, though:
  java jode.decompiler.Main 'daikon.inv.ternary.threeScalar.LinearTernaryCore$1'
(I used javap instead, which gave me a hint about it.)


# Source
cd ~/tmp/
wget http://unc.dl.sourceforge.net/sourceforge/jode/jode-1.1.2-pre1.tar.gz
tar xzf jode-1.1.2-pre1.tar.gz

===========================================================================

jad:

cd ~/tmp
wget http://kpdus.tripod.com/jad/linux/jadlx158.zip
unzip jadlx158.zip

Now
     ~/tmp/jad example1.class
creates example1.jad in the current directory.
